  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "We could call it 'direct transaction cost'  because we do not know what else happens inside the transaction. Transaction cost includes execution cost plus cost for the payload (for the constructor this is the creation code plus constructor arguments, for functions this is function selector plus arguments). Since zero bytes have a different cost, we can assume the arguments to not contain any zeros to get an upper bound.",
